complaints.summary: WHILE DRIVING AT ANY SPEEDS THE MANUAL TRANSMISSION SYNCOS WEAR OUT PREMATURELY CAUSING GRINDING INTO GEARS AND FAILURE TO ENGAGE GEARS WICH CAN CAUSE STALLS OR SUDDEN LOSS OF SPEED. IV BEEN TOLD ITS A VERY COMMON PROBLEM AMONG THESE VEHICLES.

TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2008 AUDI S5. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE AIR BAG WARNING INDICATOR ILLUMINATED AFTER THE VEHICLE WAS SERVICED PER NHTSA CAMPAIGN NUMBER: 16V376000 (AIR BAGS). THE FAILURE WAS A SAFETY CONCERN. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN BACK THE FOLLOWING DAY TO THE DEALER (AUDI OMAHA, 808 N 102ND ST, SUITE B, OMAHA, NE 68114, 402-393-7000) AND THE TECHNICIAN DENIED ANY RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE FAILURE. THE DEALER STATED THAT THE FAILURE EXISTED PRIOR TO THE RECALL REPAIRS. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED AND REFERRED THE CONTACT BACK TO THE DEALER. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS APPROXIMATELY 129,000.

TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 2008 AUDI S5. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE SIDE AIR BAG WAS LEAKING. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO A DEALER WHERE THEY ADVISED HIM THAT THE SUNROOF SHOULD HAVE DRAINED THE EXCESS WATER BUT IT WAS ENTERING THROUGH THE AIR BAG INSTEAD. THE CONTACT WAS ADVISED THAT THE SUNROOF CONNECTION WOULD NEED REPAIRING. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT CONTACTED. THE FAILURE AND CURRENT MILEAGES WERE APPROXIMATELY 32,000.

issues.title: Carbon Buildup on Intake Valves
issues.description: Direct injection engines suffer from carbon deposits on intake valves due to lack of fuel washing over valves, causing reduced performance and rough idle
issues.fix_description: Intake valve cleaning service using walnut shell blasting or chemical cleaning
issues.prevention: Regular use of quality fuel additives, occasional highway driving, consider catch can installation

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Failure
issues.description: Upper timing chain tensioner can fail, causing timing chain to skip or break, potentially leading to catastrophic engine damage
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain tensioner, guides, and chain. May require engine rebuild if damage occurred
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper specification oil, address rattling noises immediately

issues.title: PCV System Failure
issues.description: Positive Crankcase Ventilation system components fail, causing oil consumption, vacuum leaks, and rough idle
issues.fix_description: Replace PCV valve, separator, and associated hoses and diaphragms
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance intervals, use quality engine oil, replace air filter regularly

issues.title: High Pressure Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: High pressure fuel pump cam follower wears excessively, potentially damaging camshaft and causing fuel delivery issues
issues.fix_description: Replace high pressure fuel pump, cam follower, and potentially camshaft if damaged
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, monitor for metal particles in oil, early replacement of cam follower

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: Plastic impeller water pumps fail prematurely, causing coolant leaks and potential engine overheating
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump and thermostat, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, monitor coolant levels, replace at recommended intervals

issues.title: Ignition Coil Failure
issues.description: Ignition coils fail frequently, particularly on cylinders 2 and 5, causing misfires and rough running
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty ignition coils and spark plugs
issues.prevention: Replace spark plugs at recommended intervals, use quality ignition components

issues.title: DSG Transmission Mechatronic Unit Failure
issues.description: DSG transmission control module fails, causing harsh shifts, loss of gears, and transmission warning lights
issues.fix_description: Replace or rebuild mechatronic unit, update transmission software
issues.prevention: Regular DSG service intervals, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption due to worn piston rings, valve seals, or PCV system failures
issues.fix_description: Depends on root cause - PCV repair, valve seal replacement, or engine rebuild
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, quality oil, monitor consumption rates

issues.title: Supercharger Pulley Issues
issues.description: Supercharger pulley can slip or fail, reducing boost pressure and performance
issues.fix_description: Replace supercharger pulley and belt system
issues.prevention: Regular belt inspections, avoid excessive modifications

issues.title: Control Arm Bushing Wear
issues.description: Front control arm bushings wear prematurely, causing handling issues and tire wear
issues.fix_description: Replace control arms or bushings, perform wheel alignment

issues.title: Brake Pad Sensor Wiring Issues
issues.description: Brake pad wear sensor wiring becomes damaged, causing false brake warning lights
symptoms: brake pad warning when pads are good
issues.fix_description: Repair or replace brake pad sensor wiring and sensors
issues.prevention: Careful handling during brake work, protect wiring from damage

issues.title: Sunroof Drain Blockage
issues.description: Sunroof drain tubes become blocked, causing water to leak into interior and potentially damage electronics
issues.fix_description: Clear drain tubes, repair or replace damaged components, dry interior
issues.prevention: Regular cleaning of sunroof area, clear debris from drains

editorial.tagline: Supercharged sophistication with Germanic precision and soul
editorial.hero_blurb: The B8 S5 represents Audi's sweet spot between everyday usability and genuine performance thrills. With its muscular supercharged V6 and quattro grip, this coupe delivers refined power that's as comfortable on the autobahn as it is carving canyon roads.
editorial.essence: The B8 S5 is the thinking enthusiast's sports coupe, blending Audi's meticulous build quality with a properly engaging driving experience. It's sophisticated enough for the boardroom yet spirited enough to make every commute an event.
editorial.heritage: Born from Audi's reinvention of the S-line philosophy, the B8 S5 marked a shift from naturally aspirated engines to forced induction, establishing the blueprint for modern Audi performance cars while maintaining the elegant coupe proportions that made the original so desirable.
editorial.design_philosophy: Understated aggression wrapped in tailored elegance - the designers wanted a car that wouldn't shout its performance credentials but would whisper them with confidence through subtle flares, purposeful stance, and those distinctive LED daytime running lights.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct racing derivative, the S5 benefits from Audi's extensive quattro rally heritage and touring car development, with lessons learned from competition filtering down to create a balanced, confidence-inspiring road car.
editorial.engine_character: The supercharged 3.0T delivers power like a silk-wrapped sledgehammer - instant torque from idle that builds to a creamy, linear rush all the way to redline, with a mechanical whine that hints at the forced induction magic happening under the hood.
editorial.transmission_feel: The available manual gearbox offers precise, mechanical engagement with a satisfying weight to each shift, while the S tronic dual-clutch delivers lightning-quick changes that feel almost telepathic in their responsiveness.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Planted and predictable with just enough playfulness to keep things interesting, the chassis strikes an ideal balance between comfort and control, allowing the quattro system to distribute power seamlessly while maintaining composure through challenging corners.
editorial.steering_feel: Direct and communicative without being harsh, the steering provides genuine feedback about road surface and grip levels while maintaining the refinement expected from a premium German coupe.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with excellent pedal feel and fade resistance that inspire confidence during spirited driving while remaining smooth and linear for everyday use.
editorial.sound_signature: A cultured growl that builds to an authoritative roar, punctuated by the subtle supercharger whine on acceleration and satisfying pops on overrun - mechanical music that never becomes tiresome.
editorial.ideal_owner: The accomplished professional who appreciates engineering excellence and wants a car that can handle both client meetings and weekend track days without breaking a sweat or their budget.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Badge snobs seeking maximum prestige, track-focused drivers wanting razor-sharp handling over comfort, or anyone who can't appreciate the subtle art of understated performance.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with complete service records, particularly carbon cleaning intervals on the direct-injection engine. The B8 S5 offers genuine performance car thrills wrapped in daily-driver practicality at increasingly attractive prices.

expertReviews.title: Is the Audi S5 B8 Worth the Risk?
pros: 260 kW/350 hp naturally aspirated V8 engine
Manual transmission with quattro AWD
Excellent value for money at around 15k
Refined driving experience with good ride quality
Well-designed interior with practical features
Revs to 7000 RPM with great engine sound
Drives 8/10 of an RS4 for half the price
cons: Timing chain guide failure around 200k km requiring engine-out repair
Manual gearbox throws are a bit long
Steering feel could be better
Engine reliability concerns
35 buttons on dashboard can be overwhelming
expertReviews.verdict: One of the best value mid-2000s Audis available, offering V8 manual AWD performance for around 15k. The 4.2L V8 produces 350hp and excellent sound, paired with practical quattro system. Major concern is timing chain guide failure requiring expensive engine-out repair. If bought with good service history or completed chain work, it's an excellent enthusiast choice that delivers most of RS4 performance at half the cost.

expertReviews.title: What it's like to own a 2013 Audi S5 B8.5!! Drive + Walk ... by leon feinstein
pros: Timeless design inside and out
Reliable supercharged 3.0T V6 engine
Excellent tunability potential (650+ HP)
Real leather and metal materials throughout
Exceptional depreciation value ($64.5k new, bought for $26k)
Seven-speed DSG transmission reliability
Modern capabilities with CarPlay upgrade option
cons: Maintenance costs ($5-7k in repairs)
Cramped engine bay makes repairs difficult
Common issues with thermostat and water pump
Timing chain tensioner problems
AWE track exhaust can be droney
expertReviews.verdict: Owner considers this his dream car and rates it 10/10. The B8.5 S5 offers supercar performance potential, timeless design, and incredible value due to depreciation. Despite higher maintenance costs typical of German cars, the 3.0T engine is reliable once major issues are addressed. Perfect balance of performance, luxury, and practicality that modern Audis can't match.

expertReviews.title: Audi S5 Review | 4.2L V8, 2 Door, 6-Speed Manual Dream ...
pros: 4.2L V8 engine with fantastic sound and low rumble
6-speed manual transmission adds engagement
Excellent interior quality with comfortable seats and good sound system
Sleek and sporty two-door design with great body lines
All-wheel drive system provides planted feel
Luxurious and smooth ride quality even with coilovers
cons: Limited rear seat space with poor legroom and headroom
Sunroof doesn't slide back due to roof space constraints
Manual transmission not as direct as some sports cars
Exhaust modifications make it quite loud externally
expertReviews.verdict: The B8 Audi S5 is described as an 'absolutely awesome car' that combines luxury with performance. The reviewer thoroughly enjoyed the 4.2L V8 engine sound and manual transmission, praising the comfortable interior, sleek design, and smooth driving experience. Despite some practicality limitations with rear seating, it's presented as one of the reviewer's favorite cars.

expertReviews.title: NEW Audi S5 Review: It's Not What You Think It Is
pros: Strong acceleration - 0-60 in 4.5 seconds with 367 PS
Very practical with 476L boot space expanding to 1400L with seats down
Premium interior with responsive infotainment and multiple screens
Good steering feel with feedback and cohesive braking
Customizable OLED lights and driving modes
Lower price than electric S6 alternative at 68,000
cons: No longer available as a two-door coupe
Engine sound described as 'reassuring background noise' rather than exciting
Heavy at around 2 tons - 250kg heavier than previous S4
Excessive chrome styling elements throughout
Limited customization options for throttle response and brake feel
Not the most thrilling driving experience
expertReviews.verdict: The new Audi S5 (formerly S4) is a reassuring fast estate that delivers practical luxury with solid performance. While it lacks the excitement of a two-door coupe and isn't the most thrilling drive, it offers a rare ICE-powered alternative to EVs with strong acceleration, premium interior tech, and excellent practicality. At 68,000 it's more affordable than the electric S6, making it a sensible choice for those wanting petrol power in a fast family hauler.

expertReviews.title: 2015 Audi S5 B8.5 Review - Can A 10 Year Old Car Really Be ...
pros: Supercharged V6 engine with great exhaust sound and crackles
Understated design that doesn't scream for attention
Very undervalued at current market prices ($20-30k)
Analog and tactile driving experience with driver connection
Good cargo space and practicality for a coupe
Dual-zone climate control and heated seats
Instantaneous gear shifts with dual-clutch automatic
Quattro all-wheel drive system
cons: Feels heavy and cumbersome in corners
No Apple CarPlay or modern connectivity
Interior lacks Alcantara option on this model
Not as nimble as competitors like BMW 4 Series
Manual transmission extremely rare to find
Needs aftermarket modifications to look sporty
expertReviews.verdict: The 2015 Audi S5 B8.5 represents a 'hidden gem' that perfectly balances old-school German engineering with modern technology. While it may feel heavy and less agile than newer generations, it offers soul, character, and raw driving experience that modern Audis have sacrificed for mass appeal. At current market prices of $20-30k, it's very undervalued and provides excellent performance for the money, making it ideal for enthusiasts seeking an analog, tactile driving experience.

expertReviews.title: Before You Buy an Audi S5  Here's What You NEED to Know!
pros: One of the best value V8 coupes available from 5,000
Naturally aspirated 4.2L V8 with 354 horsepower and all-wheel drive
Beautiful and understated design with classy V8 rumble
Available with six-speed manual or automatic transmission
Comfortable interior with good space and storage
Quattro all-wheel drive provides confidence in winter conditions
Rare V8 model only produced for about 4 years
cons: Door lock failures common (250 to replace)
Interior wear on driver's seat bolster and start button
High running costs - 735 annual road tax, 17 mpg city/mid-20s highway
Heavy nose causes suspension component wear
Potential timing chain issues requiring replacement every 90-100k miles (3,500)
Carbon buildup requires walnut blasting service (400-650)
Expensive clutch replacement (1,300) and gearbox service every 40k miles
Common issues with coil packs, fuel pumps, injectors, and coolant leaks
expertReviews.verdict: The B8 Audi S5 with V8 engine offers exceptional value as a performance coupe, but requires a maintenance fund beyond purchase price. The naturally aspirated 4.2L V8 with Quattro AWD provides a rare combination at this price point. Most examples have been modified or abused, making unmolested cars increasingly valuable. Buyer should budget additional thousands for preventive maintenance including timing chain service, carbon cleaning, and addressing common issues like door locks and suspension components.
